Using the repository analysis, generate an ARCHITECTURE.md for this repository.

Purpose:
This document should help both engineers and AI agents quickly understand how the system is structured.

Include these sections when they are supported by the repository contents:
- System overview
- Repository structure
- Core modules/services
- Key data flows
- Technology stack
- Architectural patterns
- External dependencies and integrations
- Risk-sensitive areas

Guidelines:
- Be concise and factual
- Prefer bullet points over long paragraphs
- Base everything on the repository contents
- Do not speculate about missing components
- Omit sections that are not supported by evidence
- Keep the file under ~200 lines
- Do not include implementation instructions or agent behavior rules

Output only the final ARCHITECTURE.md content.